<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,329,534]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,329,354]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A dark reddish brown, elongate species with yellowish wings, which can be distinguished from other Madagascan species of 
<taxonomicName box="[431,540,365,389]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[431,540,365,389]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Microdon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of a yellow face and a fascia of golden pile along the posterior margin of tergite 
<number box="[452,466,401,425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[481,550,401,426]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1810,1833]" captionTargetBox="[158,1415,631,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,586,1789]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Microdon berobaka Reemer sp. n. Male holotype. 7. Habitus dorsal. 8. Habitus lateral. 9. Head frontal. 10. Genitalia lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243182/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">
Fig. 
<number box="[533,550,401,425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
